The most expensive and popular area of New York City. This is the location of the Dominion Trade Centre, which is popular with traders and merchants, as well as the capital city of the Dominion. This is the location of the Dominion Headquarters, as well as the Dominion Senate’s chambers.
The eastern part of NYC, with its famous Botanical Garden and big Brooklyn Space Harbor. Natural influences and modern architecture signify this area.

The city-habitat of Tokyo encompasses a vast myriad of styles and architecture, and the same can be said of its inhabitants. From the high tech district of Otaku with Club 69 and the Abandoned FDC Headquarters, to the old fishing port of Shibuya, and the scenic parks of Kamitakada, Tokyo has it all. Watch out for the Brotherhood!

Rehabilitation grounds for newly cloned Dominion citizens located on New York City. These sky plateaus will always be safe, regardless of the security situation in the rest of New York City. Use of weaponry is forbidden here.

A planet with vast expanses of lush greenery and incredible landscape. Discovered by the DSS Indomitable in 2413 on the furthest reaches of the edge of the Milky Way galaxy. Because the atmosphere is perfect for human inhabitation, there was no need for terraforming.

This quaint and beautiful city displays the rustic fusion of ancient 19th century buildings such as the Eiffel Tower and the Arc de Triomphe with modern 25th century architecture and technology. An ever-popular destination for aficionados of ancient European architecture and young lovebirds alike, it has recently been favored for the headquarters of corporations since the recent refurbishment of the business district.

After decades of violent uprising and unlawfulness, this city was transformed into a desolate wasteland characterized by anarchy. Although the Dominion tried desperately to seal off access, insurgents eventually overwhelmed these efforts, forcibly reconnecting the vortex link to the outside world. The observation probes that automatically detect murders and assign penalty points were also discovered and destroyed, making it a degenerate abyss of crime.

The districts Kamitakada and Shibuya make up Lower Tokyo, sitting in what remains of the original city. On the far side of Japan, most citizens live in poverty and crime is the number one way to make a living. Though, in a place like this, you can hardly call it that.

Named after the Andromeda galaxy, located on the very Mars-like moon, Omega 15. To maintain an inhabitable atmosphere for man while the rest of the moon undergoes terraforming, it has an invisible force-shield surrounding it. Due to the size limitations of this shield, the city colony has been constructed to be more compact than usual.
New Haven was the first human colony beyond our own star system. Years after colonization has been started colonists discovered massive mineral and ore deposits, especially Titanium.
Ganymede is named after one of Jupiter's moons. The complex is located in the Isis Area and is a sole mining complex. Ganymede's surface conceals many crystalline minerals and iron ores.

DeMorgan's Castle is a prison colony and mining resort. It became necessary to build a new prison colony as the far smaller prisons on its neighbor colony Constantinople were filled past capacity over the years.
Keplers Dome is located on the Moon Antares orbiting around Planet Gliese 229 B. The CMG established a colony here due to the massive mineral and ore deposits present on this colony.
The Moon Base was mankind's first outer space colony on another planet or moon. The Moon's surface offers natural materials to make the colony independent from Earth.
The Genesis Station is the gateway to space beyond our star system. It has huge industrial storage facilities and many take off and landing platforms for transporters and space cruisers.

Standing as a beacon of hope for the future and in memory of all that has been lost in history, this city has been called the Soul of the Dominion. Home to the L.E.D. Headquarters, Chinatown, Statue of Liberty, Ground Zero Memorial, and more, the sprawling streets of this great city have a universal appeal.
The colony on Mars was named after Terrence M. Booker. Booker's Valley is located within the Tharsis area, not far from Labyrinthus Noctis and the legendary Olympus Mons.
With around 10 light years the Epsilon Eridani system is very near to Earth. It is a sole ice planet with surface temperatures from -5 down to -100 °C.
The earth-type rocky moon Terra is located very close to the planet Gliese 876 B, since the habitable zone is very limited.
The Planet Exodus is a mixture of Earth and Mars and could easily be terraformed. Now it is one of the most interesting colony worlds for the future of mankind.
Espen Paradise is a mobile station over the surface of the planet's moon Espen. Its fantastic landscape  was the reason to build a vacation colony there named Espen Paradise.
Aquatica is located on an Ice Moon, surrounded by water. There is a border none of the colonists may cross, which is called 'The Big Wall'. Nobody ever returned from behind it.

51 Pegasi B is a massive planet orbiting at a distance of only 0.05 Aus from its sun. Although it is very tectonically active, the CMG established a colony here on a rock plateau where it is safe from the volcanic oceans.

The moon Aurelia is the outermost moon in orbit around a planet orbiting Sirius A. A world with a warm climate, but with little vegetation. It is only a matter of time before life finds its own way here.

Located deep in the furthest reaches of the Outer Rim territories colonized by Dominion forces is Pax, a moon orbiting the large planet 79 Ceti B, which is covered entirely with a sea of liquid oxygen, making it appear a deep, majestic blue. Pax Prime is the most distant colony from Earth to date, and is the apple of mankind's eye, being developed on massive precious mineral deposits.

Built on a watery planet. On the outside, this colony looks desolate and rundown. However, appearances can be deceiving. The interior of this colony is very modern and well-maintained, with the sound of heavy boots echoing loudly through the narrow and winding corridors as Dominion soldiers patrol the outpost.

Eons of volcanic activity have given this planet its unique terrain. However, with the establishment of a colony, a new dominant force has arrived to make its mark – man. The large underground caverns are rich with many precious minerals and this outpost is remote enough for anyone looking to evade the Dominion authorities until the heat is off.

You currently have %1!u! Penalty Points (in short PP). You will recieve Penalty Points for illegal behavior such as killing neutral/allied faction members or members of your own faction, and for carrying illegal items if scanned by a member of the Law Enforcement Department. To avoid gaining Penalty Points communicate regularly with you faction leadership for guidance and always make sure to know who your enemies are. 

The top ten citizens with PP are considered 'Most Wanted'. As a Most Wanted you will be hunted by the Law Enforcement Department as a high profile criminal. To reduce your Penalty Points find your nearest Law Enforcement Officer and surrender to be transported to DeMorgan's Castle Prison Colony. Once there, use the provided Mining Tool to work off your Penalty Points.

Your health. When it drops to 0%%, your character dies. If you have clones available upon death, you will be transferred to the Cloning Facility. However, if you have no more clones left, your character will die permanently.

Furthermore, upon each death your character will lose the items in your inventory. Equipment will remain on your character's body, but armor will be damaged and dropped.
Your current stamina. When this runs out you'll no longer be able to jump or sprint. You may replenish stamina quickly at a medical terminal, by resting briefly.

Your bio energy level. This is your body's excess natural energy that can be used to power mechanical augmentations.  When you run out of bio energy these augmentations will no longer function, you may replenish it with bio cell items or at a medical terminal.

Your aura. This is your body's combined state of perception. All your senses form an invisible aura around your body. It defines your body's ability to execute control over your body and understand information. Vision blurs when Aura is below 30%%.

Stun weaponry can negatively affect your aura.

When your aura is reduced to it's lowest point you will be 'stunned' and vulnerable to arrest by law enforcement officers.

Your Universal Credits (UC) can be used to pay on the market for items, for mining, for production, or to aid you with whatever your goals may be. You may earn Universal Credits through work within a faction, by completing contracts, by production and selling through markets, or through various other methods.

Your Faction Credits (FC) are credits that you receive from your faction for your work by completing objectives. You can not pay on the market or trade with them. Faction Credits will be evaluated daily and converted into Universal Credits at around the time 00:00.

Your Penalty Points (PP). These points are calculated based on how much crime you have committed against another being. The higher this amount, the more likely law enforcement will want to arrest you, and the longer you can stay imprisoned for if arrested.

Prisoner Status. You are currently a prisoner in DeMorgan's Castle after being arrested. When your Penalty Point amount reaches zero you will no longer be a prisoner and will be free to leave. Reduce the amount through various tasks, including using your given mining gun and submitting the minerals you collect from in the mines.
The highest penalty point value you've earned without being freed or working off your penalty.
Most-Wanted Status. This marks you as one of the top ten individuals with the most Bounty and Penalty Points in the universe.
Wanted Status. This marks you as one of the top ten individuals with the most Bounty or Penalty Points in the universe.
The Agility attribute defines how fast your character is able to run.
Ballistic damage reduces your health and is caused by ballistic weapons, knifes, and grenades. Fall damage and xenomorph attacks are also ballistic damage.
Energy damage reduces your health and is caused by energy weaponry.
Bio damage reduces your bio energy level and is caused by various weapons, explosives (such as EMP's), or illegal substances.
Aura damage reduces your aura level and is caused by stun weapons, explosives, or illegal substances.
Destruction is a damage measurement that defines damage on machinery, such as turrets. Destruction is caused by various weapons or explosives.
The weapon recoil attribute changes the ease of aiming your weapon when you're moving.
Armor is the sum of the body's protection from all equipped items against ballistic damage.
Shielding is the sum of the body's protection from all equipped items against energy damage.
Resistance is a measurement of the body's protection against bio damage.
Reflection is a measurement of the body's protection against aura damage.
Health Regeneration is the factor that increases the regeneration of health. It can be increased by using various medikits, injectors, illegal substances, or even certain equipment.

Stamina Regeneration is the factor that increases the regeneration of stamina. It can be increased by using various medikits, injectors, illegal substances, or even certain equipment. Stamina regeneration is also increased when your character is resting (standing still, sitting or lying down).
Bio Regeneration is the factor that increases the regeneration of the body's bio energy level. It can be increased by using bio cells, injectors or illegal substances.
Aura Regeneration is the factor that increases the regeneration of aura. It can be increased by using various foods or illegal substances.
Current number of tokens available to buy items at the Face of Mankind Marketplace.
Xeno damage reduces health of Xenomorphs and is caused by weapons, knifes, and grenades.
Health Drain is a measurement of health reduction caused by equipment or booster effects.
Stamina Drain is a measurement of stamina reduction caused by equipment or booster effects.
Bio Energy Drain is a measurement of bio energy reduction caused by equipment or booster effects.
Aura Loss is a measurement of aura reduction caused by equipment or booster effects.
Protection Bypass will allow your weapon to bypass the armor protection of others, based on the percentage displayed.
The range at which your weapon begins to loses effectiveness.
The rate at which your weapon fires.
The weight of all the items you are carrying.
The number of seconds that will be added onto the duration of any medikit used on yourself or others.
This multiplier effects the height and speed at which you can jump
This multiplier effects the amount of damage you receive from falling long distances.
If enabled, your vision will be nightvision.
If enabled, your movement will make no sound.
The distance at which you are able to interact with objects in the world.
This multiplier effects the speed of sprinting.
The ubiquitous subsidized public housing provided by the Global Dominion's Department of Housing and Development.
Built for the absolute poorest of society. Typically offers the most basic of amenities, although disliked for its shoddy workmanship.
A very low-cost housing solution for the immense numbers of Colonization and Mining Guild workers assigned to terraform the colonies.
A modest, but stylish apartment. Features very subtle French architecture which gives it a unique appearance.
A fair-sized apartment that utilizes traditional Japanese construction materials and techniques, giving it a unique and serene appearance.
Severely lacking in space, the Underwater Flat is reminiscent of a space-constrained submarine, albeit more with more stylish furnishings.
Considered to be good value for money consider the large floor space for its relatively low price. Its architecture is typical of residences in Manhattan.
Despite its dilapidated appearance, this apartment offers all the creature comforts necessary for day-to-day living at rock-bottom prices.
This relatively spacious apartment still betrays the harsh colonial environment it was constructed for through its utilitarian and drab architecture.
A very well-furnished apartment with French design, this apartment is built for comfort with the latest household appliances and furniture included.
A distinctive Japanese atmosphere can be found in this apartment through its warm lighting provided by traditional lanterns and wooden architecture.
Considering the architectural difficulties of building underwater dwellings, this apartment impresses with its size and modern design, reinforcing the surrealism of living underwater.
A much sought-after apartment characteristic of those found on Manhattan. It is known for its modern and sensible style, emanating warmth and comfort.
A staple of heavily industrialized areas on both Earth and the colonies. Popular with undesirable elements of society despite its relatively spartan and industrial architecture.
Although lacking in aesthetics, the Colonial Suite designed for the top managers of the Colonization and Mining Guild's terraforming projects on the colonies boasts a large floor space.
Featuring with a two-storey design with ample floor space often used for parties under a massive skylight allowing a panoramic view of the night sky.
Designed by famed architect Fukuzawa Yuuichi, resembling the opulent housing of the ancient samurai in Japan, but with significant stylistic touches reflecting the present.
The largest underwater dwelling built to alleviate the burgeoning problem of land shortages. Features large portholes for a stunning view of the oceans.
Favored by organizations operating on the fringes of the law, built 0.5km underground with industrial level utilities that allows extended periods of seclusion from society.
Replete with state-of-the-art equipment and facilities that facilitate effective command and control over tactical situations.
The perfect picture of opulence and excess favored by the Dominion's mega-corporations as a luxurious gathering place for their top executives.
Once the prize of the Dominion military, the Arcturus class battle freighter features everything from training facilities to communications systems, making it the perfect base of operations.
Originally created as an extension to the DeMorgan's Castle Prison Colony, this module has instead been mass produced for distribution as an apartment in an effort to minimize public conflict.
A luxurious apartment filled with the subtleties of any modern home.

Your clones physical abilities need to be up to par in order to use any military grade equipment.
Sacrificing the higher ballistic protection stats, lighter armor allows you to move more quickly and freely in combat.
Although slowing you more than other armors, heavy ballistic armor allows you to sustain more hits from ballistic weapons than the lighter armors classes.
Beyond just typical ballistic armor protection, other types in production allow for more specific purposes, but require more advanced training to use.
The more experience one gains in combat, the greater their efficient use of armor is.
The training of ones body to its physical limitations will give the strength necessary to carry equipment with less of a penalty.
Sacrificing the higher energy protection stats, lighter armor allows you to move more quickly and freely in combat.
Although slowing you more than other armors, heavy energy armor allows you to sustain more hits from energy weapons than the lighter armors classes.
The more experience one gains in combat, the greater their efficient use of armor is.
The stress on ones body from energy-based armor is more extensive, and requires augmentation to overcome.
The reverse engineering and manipulation of computer systems will allow the user access otherwise reserved for those with the correct credentials.
Through the manipulation of the same technology that allows for universal travel, entrance to apartments can be tracked and repeated with the correct tools.
The initialization of the most advanced hacking systems money can buy requires extensive training and education.
This skill prepares ones clone for the use of mechanical augmentations that would otherwise short circuit.
This skill prepares ones clone for the use of nanomachine augmentations that would otherwise short circuit.

As standard a handgun as will be found in The Dominion, the Inflex can take standard 9mm ammo. Originally produced by Isotech, it is now widely constructed (often illegally) due to its wide design. (Class I weapon)

A handgun for the new age. Accurate, lightweight, quiet and efficient- the Ryx 7 is the sidearm of choice for countless security forces. Using energy cells ensures a power source is never far away. (Class I weapon)
Knives require a special curveture in ones hands to be used at maximum efficiency. (Class I weapon)
A tough, durable submachine gun, the Techtronic has seen heavy use by the less sociable elements of The Dominion. This weapon uses 6mm rounds. (Class I weapon)

One of the most powerful projectile weapons widely available. Used heavily by Dominion Military, the RGI-9 combines accuracy and firepower in a single package, with the inclusion of a 3x scope. (Class II weapon)

Pain is the Infineon's trademark. Lethal beams of energy, the same as is used in vortex technology, are used to literally rip the target to shreads at the molecular level, causing untold agony. (Class II weapon)

A 'tazer' of kinds that have been seen for centuries. By passing uncountable levels of electricity through a victim, it renders the target incapacitated. Effectiveness is reduced against armoured targets. (Class II weapon)
Hand grenade by Federated Arms, causing a heavy hot fusion reaction, and operates on a five second fuse. (Class II weapon)

Grenade by Militek Electronics, causing a heavy electro-magnetic pulse. Drains the bio-electrical supply of those caught in the blast, terminating implants until they can be recharged. Uses a five second fuse. (Class II weapon)

Hallem Industries' famed high-powered sniper rifle specially reinforced through molecular reconstruction to withstand the pressure of the large-caliber rounds custom made for this weapon. Featuring a 7x zoom scope, the TAR7 has been adopted officially by the Freedom Defense Corps for use by infantry sharpshooters. (Class II weapon)

Part of Chrono Incorporated's latest series of Enervon weapons intended for tactical use. This line of weapons is unique in being able to drain a target's stamina and bioenergy through the use of superheated electrons. The EP24 is designed with close quarters combat in mind, being one of the more portable and compact weapons of the Enervon line of weapons. (Class II weapon)

The Linner PP7 is a rifle developed specifically for mid range combat. It is amongst the most accurate of the rifles due to its constant, measured rate of fire. The PP7 also inflicts higher amounts of damage per projectile as opposed to a projectile fired from the RGI 9. In the right hands, it can be as lethal if not more lethal than any other ballistic weapon. It uses reinforced 7.62mm ammunition and is also equipped with a 5x scope. (Class III weapon)

After intense competition between rival arms manufacturers in the concussion grenade market, Salvotec emerged from the fray with the HP220, subsequently monopolizing the market with its unprecedented damage, almost zero rate-of-failure, and overall reliability in battlefield conditions. Popularly used by anti-Dominion forces for harassment purposes after a glut in the market caused the prices for the HP220 to fall drastically, making it relatively easily obtainable. (Class III weapon)
Electromagnetic pulse grenade designed to counter prevalent use of bioimplants by draining the bioenergy of any personnel caught in the blast. (Class III weapon)
Gakk Industries' mainstay lightweight sub-machine gun utilising ballistic rounds; featuring high-capacity magazines and high rate-of-fire. (Class III weapon)

The Former CEO of Gakk Technology Henry Wakemen has released newly founded Protonix Industries first sidearm. The Barracuda is aimed at taking on rival company Enfield using an old ballistic style firing system which the company says will ensure the safety of those targetted. It's a non-lethal civil enforcement armament, designed for use by GD personnel at close range to knock the fighting ability out of a target. (Class III weapon)

A new entrant into the arms business, Aurelian Technologies released their new developmental rifle that is designed to destabilise the biocell energy stored by a persons body and prevent them from using implants, as well as disrupting their thought process and brain impulses, allowing easier control of the subject. Includes a 4x scope. (Class III weapon)

The medigun fires a stream of nano particles at the target which heals damaged tissue and ligaments. This device by CryoTech Industries is revolutionary in being lightweight and compact enough to be fit in your pocket. It is not intended to heal serious wounds and you should seek further medical help from a registered medic terminal. (Class III weapon)
Created using a reverse temperature polarization technique, this energy rifle fires at a faster rate and deals stamina damage. (Class III weapon)
The ubiquitous energy pistol by Gakk Industries which discharges the distinctive particles characteristic of the HR420. Popular with civilians for its reliability and affordability. (Class IV weapon)

One of Enfield Corporation's latest law enforcement weapons in the Incapacitator series designed and produced according to custom specifications provided by the Law Enforcement Department and Freedom Defense Corps. Produced specially to meet the growing demands by Global Dominion forces for a non-lethal weapon that is able to minimise risk of injury to law enforcers by having a greatly increased effective range over existing weapons. Includes a 2x scope. (Class IV weapon)

The medigun fires a stream of nano particles at the target which heals damaged tissue and ligaments. This device by CryoTech Industries is revolutionary in being lightweight and compact enough to be deployed for tactical usage on the battlefield. It is not intended to heal serious wounds and you should seek further medical help from a registered medic terminal. (Class IV weapon)

After extensive research by archaeologists on Necars Field, ancient alien technology unrelated to the current xenomorphs was discovered. Defense scientists subsequently learned how to replicate the weapon and found it to be light, yet durable and bearing a considerable ability to penetrate xenomorph carapace with relative ease using a ballistic projectile encapsulated by a shroud of special energy particles. (Class IV weapon)

Utilizing a special type of 9mm round, this illegal modification of the Zanathid 5 Inflex is capable of piercing any time of armor on the market. Meant as a weapon able to be used against those with significant armor, it certainly packs a punch. (Class IV weapon)
Popularly known as simply 'DOA', this Techtronic weapon discharges supercharged particles which are hot enough to cauterize flesh and melt the highest grades of armor. (Class V weapon)

Created using Hallem's experimental compression technology, this limited production rifle compresses a beam of energy into a single particle and accelerates it. The heat generated by the weapon is quickly absorbed by the carbon nanotube casing, preventing most cases of overheating and allowing for faster shots than its ballistic counterpart. (Class V weapon)
Created by American Enterprises, this amazing piece of technology is capable of killing Xenomorphs and humans alike, without requiring the same effort and ability as other weapons. (Class V weapon)

Combatants are skilled warriors trained to have the upper hand in combat situations. A Combatant is someone to fear when going up against them. Combatants are important to factions by not only being a skilled warrior, but holding their own in a fight. They can use their wit and strength to persevere through any obstacle.

An Entrepreneur is not only a salesman, but has a keen sense of battle.

An infiltrator is a stealthy, sly, hacker that has been assigned a mission to create war, or to loot an apartment for personal gain. They are skilled at getting past codes and other road blocks in his/her way. Known for their remarkable success at getting past codes, they are also known as thieves. An Infiltrator can be the gateway to war, or losing possessions in a person’s apartment.

Medical Technicians are known for their survivability during fights, and their swift healing for either themselves or others.

Bounty Hunters set the stage for eliminating people that stand in a faction’s way, or could plummet a faction into war.

Hello Citizen and welcome to Face of Mankind!

During your journey through the Universe you will encounter many different kinds of people with different goals. Face of Mankind is all about social interaction, so try to communicate with other players and work together to achieve goals. You can find open faction applications in the faction manager tab. Factions pay/support their members while working toward a common goal.

Players and factions gain power through economic and militaristic force. In order to produce items one must first obtain raw materials. These can be found by using a mining tool or mining rig to extract minerals from rock surfaces on designated mining colonies/areas. These minerals can be recycled for a small amount of Universal Credits or refined into goods use schematics.

Players can also specialize in different types of weapons and armor to perform better in combat. Those who excel in combat can invest in tracking and start accepting bounty contracts through the bounty manager. Some players will be known for their excellent espionage skills. World Services, barriers, loot packs, and apartments all need to be hacked in order to control or access them. There are different security levels, so different types of hacking devices and different class devices are required.

After you complete character creation and leave your apartment, you will be sent to New York City - Brooklyn. There, you will find a tutorial NPC which will teach you all of the basics, and give you the skills, money, and equipment you'll need to get started in the world.

Welcome to Face of Mankind. These hints will help you learn more about the game. 

Important Keybinds:
Run/Walk Toggle: <font color='FFE6BF00'>%1!s!</font>
Lay down: <font color='FFE6BF00'>%2!s!</font>
Sit: <font color='FFE6BF00'>%3!s!</font>
Fullscreen Map: <font color='FFE6BF00'>%4!s!</font>
Switch Chat: <font color='FFE6BF00'>%5!s!</font>

For the rest of the keybinds in the game, please review the controls section of the options.
Please press <font color='FFE6BF00'>ESC</font> and hit next for a short interface introduction.
Pressing this button will open the skill manager. These skills will allow you to gain access to new equipment and tools, in addition to enhancing your abilities.

Pressing this button will open the faction manager. Through this, you will be able to apply for a faction and become part of something far greater than yourself.

By default, you are a member of Dolly Incorporated. This is a faction comprised of new players and volunteers, so feel free to use the 'Dolly Inc' chat tab to ask for assistance or to meet other players.
We recommend after you get a grasp of the game's mechanics you join a different faction, as Dolly Inc does not participate in typical game activities.

If being a follower does not suit you, then you will be able to create your own faction after training the 'Badge of Valor' skill.
Pressing this button will open the mission manager. Utilizing this interface, you will be able to lead and join groups of clones in missions to complete goals defined by the leader.
Pressing this button will open the communicator. Through this, you will be able to send messages to other clones, in addition to accessing the in-game browser, calculator, and various other tools.

Pressing this button will open the bounty manager. This manager will allow you to create, manage, and accept bounties. Bounties are created by clones, and will call for the assassination of another individual.
Pressing this button will open the options menu. This will allow you to make changes to your graphics, sound, interface, and control settings.

You have died!

Death in Face of Mankind is a common occurance, and should not be too discouraging. On death, you will drop any items on your person that are not secured or bound to you. They will be dropped into a loot pack, which by default, has a 3 minute timer to reclaim the items. After the timer has ended, or the lootpack has been hacked, the items are free for anyone to steal.

Each time you die, your death timer will increase. You may either wait until the timer has completed, or alternatively spend credits/coins to immediately complete the cloning process.

This is your skill manager. Once you have used a skill book, the skill will be available here to train. In the bottom right is your active queue, and contains all of the skills currently progressing.

To queue a skill, it must be yellow in the interface. Right click on it and add it to your queue. Once queued, a skill will be marked to progress once it reaches the top of the queue. Skills progress while offline.

This is the storage interface. There are two types of Storage in Face of Mankind; Item Storage and Transport Storage.

Item storage is only available on certain worlds, but offers a safe place to store your good at a relatively low cost. In the bottom left of item storages you will find the rental management panel. Here, you will be able to decide how many rental units you wish to purchase. Each in-game week, you will be charged the rental fee for your storage. If your account does not have sufficient funds, your items will be given another week. If you cannot pay the fee by the end of the week, the items will be sent to transport storage.

Transport storage is a temporary form of storage meant to allow users a way to transport items from worlds that do not have storage. Each item has a timeout, after which it will be removed. To retrieve the item after it has timed out, you must use the transport buyback option, available at the bottom of the interface.

This is the apartment safe interface. You may drag items into the interface to store them here, and they will remain after you have left. Each apartment has a safe, which is accessible both to the owner, and to hackers who have managed to infiltrate the apartment. Any items taken from the safe are logged, and can be viewed by scanning the safe with a Hunter augmentation.

This is the production manager. Using this, you will be able to create almost any item in the game. To produce an item, you must place a production schematic into the top left, and then fill in all of the items for the recipe.

At an additional cost, you may alternatively place the ingredients into storage. Pressing the 'Fill from storage' option at the bottom of the interface will cause the system to auto-fill the recipe with items in your item storage or transport storage, depending on what the world has available. Please note however that this does cost additional.

Refining may be done without a schematic, at an additional cost. Simple press the dropdown in the bottom left and select the item that you wish to refine.

Once a process has started, you may check on its progress through the second tab at the top of the production interface.

This is a market. Using this, you will be able to purchase goods from other clones, or sell them if you desire.

To purchase, simple apply any appropriate search filters, and find the item that you would like to purchase. After selecting the item and an offer, use the bottom left to select quantity and preview cost.

To sell, press the storage button in the bottom left to open a special version of the storage interface. This special version contains a market offer section, and will allow you to place items on the market from your transport storage.

This is a schematic market. These markets allow you to purchase production schematics. After selecting the type of schematic you wish to purchase, use the buttons in the bottom left to decide how many items the resulting schematic can produce. Once you have produced that many items with the schematic, it will be depleted, and you will have to purchase another.

This is a medical station. Using this, you are able to install augmentations and receive basic medical treatment. To install an augmentation, simply drag it into the install section and press the button.

To remove an already installed augmentation, right click it in the list and remove it.

This is the chemical lab. Using this, you will be able to create chemicals, food, and drugs. Food and drugs are created using special formulas, which can only be utilized once you have the necessary skill trained.

To use, simply bring your chemical substances to the world service. Once here, enter the formula that you wish to produce and begin. Please note that during the process you may not leave the area, as doing so will cause it to fail.

This is the mission manager. Using this, you will be able to create and join missions.

To create a mission, you must have funds. You may enter in a name and description for it, along with adding access restrictions to the mission. You will be able to define the rewards, and manage the members from here. Once the mission begins, you will also be able to view the log, which contains information about what has happened in the mission.

Once a mission has completed, it must be reviewed before the reward is delivered. Through the mission review tab, you may view and approve/disapprove the rewards of a mission based on whether or not it completed the goals that you defined for it.

This is the repair station. Using this, you are able to repair any items that has lost durability. Please note that when you repair an item using credits, the durability loss factor will increase, causing the item to lose durability faster.

This is the apartment manager. Using this, you will be able to purchase and enter private apartments, as well as view and enter public apartments. Once purchased, these apartments will be accessible from anywhere in the game world. Public apartments are apartments that have been opened to everyone, and do not require a password to enter.

Please be warned! When entering an apartment or logging off, you are susceptible to infiltration scanners. If a scan is successfully completed, hackers will be able to enter your apartment and potentially steal your items from the apartment safe inside!

This is the bounty manager. Using this, you will be able to place, manage, and take bounties.

Once you have created a bounty, hunters will be able to apply to complete it. You will be able to review their bounty history and decide whether or not you want them to take the bounty. Once approved, they will be able to hunt down your target and kill them. If they successfully kill the target, they will have their reward delivered. If they are killed by the target however, a portion will be given to the target.

You have been arrested!

While you are here, your penalty points will statically decrease until you reach 10% of the value that you had when you were arrested. You have two choices when it comes to leaving. You may either pay the bail and leave immediately, or you may mine rocks to work off your debt.

Bail may be paid by finding one of the designated bail terminals. Rocks may be mined using the prison-sanctioned mining tool, and depositing the rocks into a nearby mineral collector. The more rocks that you mine, the more penalty points that will be removed by the collector.
Filled with xenomorphs, this world is a dangerous wasteland. Xenomorphs may be killed to earn universal credits, but it is an activity not advised for the weak of heart.

This is the multicom. From here, you will be able to change information about your character, and give access to others. If you have the correct faction rank permission, you may make it into a faction HQ, and allow anyone of the appropriate rank inside. You may also make it public, and allow anyone who desires access. Perhaps you want to open a bar; anything is possible through public apartments.

Your Emergency Shield has been triggered!

This special shield will automatically activate when charged, protection you from damage for five seconds. After the shield has activated it will be unavailable for five minutes or until your death, whichever comes first. You may view the current status of your Emergency Shield in the top-left of your HUD, next to the stamina bar. When active, it will be a green shield, and when recharging, it will be red.

Be warned: after your first 24 hours of online time, the Emergency Shield will only trigger under specific circumstances. These include being unarmed (only carrying a mining gun, alien gun, or medical weapon), and while viewing a world service or territory deployable. If attacked without meeting this criteria, your shield will not activate!
This button will open your character sheet. From here, you can view information about your character and access your inventory.

This button will open the forum in the in-game browser. After logging in using your game account, you will be able to view the bug tracker and community-driven development. From here, you will be able to contribute to the development of the game by making suggestions and voting on the suggestions of other players, helping carve out future patches to the game.

A handgun for the new age. Accurate, lightweight, quiet and efficient- the Ryx 7 is the sidearm of choice for countless security forces. Using energy cells ensures a power source is never far away.
One of the most powerful projectile weapons widely available. Used heavily by Dominion Military, the RGI-9 combines accuracy and firepower in a single package, with the inclusion of a 3x scope.
Pain is the Infineon's trademark. Lethal beams of energy, the same as is used in vortex technology, are used to literally rip the target to shreads at the molecular level, causing untold agony.
Standard double-edged combat knife, designed by Federated Arms. A true warrior's tool.

A 'tazer' of kinds that have been seen for centuries. By passing uncountable levels of electricity through a victim, it renders the target incapacitated. Effectiveness is reduced against armoured targets.
Hand grenade by Federated Arms, causing a heavy hot fusion reaction, and operates on a five second fuse.

Grenade by Militek Electronics, causing a heavy electro-magnetic pulse. Drains the bio-electrical supply of those caught in the blast, terminating augmentations until they can be recharged. Uses a five second fuse.
A tough, durable submachine gun, the Techtronic has seen heavy use by the less sociable elements of The Dominion. This weapon uses 6mm rounds.
The ubiquitous energy pistol by Gakk Industries which discharges the distinctive particles characteristic of the HR420. Popular with civilians for its reliability and affordability.

The Linner PP7 is a rifle developed specifically for mid range combat. It is amongst the most accurate of the rifles due to its constant, measured rate of fire. The PP7 also inflicts higher amounts of damage per projectile as opposed to a projectile fired from the RGI 9. In the right hands, it can be as lethal if not more lethal than any other ballistic weapon. It uses reinforced 7.62mm ammunition and is also equipped with a 5x scope.

Popularly known as simply 'DOA', this Techtronic weapon discharges supercharged particles which are hot enough to cauterize flesh and melt the highest grades of armor. Note: This weapon is not available for trainees!

After intense competition between rival arms manufacturers in the concussion grenade market, Salvotec emerged from the fray with the HP220, subsequently monopolizing the market with its unprecedented damage, almost zero rate-of-failure, and overall reliability in battlefield conditions. Popularly used by anti-Dominion forces for harassment purposes after a glut in the market caused the prices for the HP220 to fall drastically, making it relatively easily obtainable. Note: This weapon is not available for trainees!
Electromagnetic pulse grenade designed to counter prevalent use of bioaugmentations by draining the bioenergy of any personnel caught in the blast. Note: This weapon is not available for trainees!
Gakk Industries' mainstay lightweight sub-machine gun utilising ballistic rounds; featuring high-capacity magazines and high rate-of-fire.

Hallem Industries' famed high-powered sniper rifle specially reinforced through molecular reconstruction to withstand the pressure of the large-caliber rounds custom made for this weapon. Featuring a 7x zoom scope, the TAR7 has been adopted officially by the Freedom Defense Corps for use by infantry sharpshooters. Note: This weapon is not available for trainees!

The Former CEO of Gakk Technology Henry Wakemen has released newly founded Protonix Industries first sidearm. The Barracuda is aimed at taking on rival company Enfield using an old ballistic style firing system which the company says will ensure the safety of those targetted. It's a non-lethal civil enforcement armament, designed for use by GD personnel at close range to knock the fighting ability out of a target.

Part of Chrono Incorporated's latest series of Enervon weapons intended for tactical use. This line of weapons is unique in being able to drain a target's stamina and bioenergy through the use of superheated electrons. This phenomenon was an unexpected discovery made by Chrono Incorporated's medical wing's experiments in the use of such superheated electrons for oncological purposes. The EP24 is designed with close quarters combat in mind, being one of the more portable and compact weapons of the Enervon line of weapons.

A new entrant into the arms business, Aurelian Technologies released their new developmental rifle that is designed to destabilise the biocell energy stored by a persons body and prevent them from using augmentations, as well as disrupting their thought process and brain impulses, allowing easier control of the subject. Includes a 4x scope.

One of Enfield Corporation's latest law enforcement weapons in the Incapacitator series designed and produced according to custom specifications provided by the Law Enforcement Department and Freedom Defense Corps. Produced specially to meet the growing demands by Global Dominion forces for a non-lethal weapon that is able to minimise risk of injury to law enforcers by having a greatly increased effective range over existing weapons. Includes a 2x scope.

The medigun fires a stream of nano particles at the target which heals damaged tissue and ligaments. This device by CryoTech Industries is revolutionary in being lightweight and compact enough to be deployed for tactical usage on the battlefield. It is not intended to heal serious wounds and you should seek further medical help from a registered medic terminal.
Utilizing advanced energy weaponry, this deployable object allows you to build stationary defense positions, attacking targets based on circumstances that you define in the confugration.

After extensive research by archaeologists on Necars Field, ancient alien technology unrelated to the current xenomorphs was discovered. Defense scientists subsequently learned how to replicate the weapon and found it to be light, yet durable and bearing a considerable ability to penetrate xenomorph carapace with relative ease using a ballistic projectile encapsulated by a shroud of special energy particles.
The most basic mining tool available; this firearm is capable of mining various resources from rock surfaces, depending on what is available where it is fired.
A mining tool manufactured for the sole purpose of mining higher class minerals to create more advanced objects.

In an attempt to raise brand awareness, Salvotec Industries releases this specialty weapon. Not only does this grenade deal quite a blow, it also serves as an over the top warning to those around that you mean business.
Created to celebrate the Halloween season, Salvotec Industries releases this fantastically painted modification of their flagship grenade.

Created using Hallem's experimental compression technology, this limited production rifle compresses a beam of energy into a single particle and accelerates it. The heat generated by the weapon is quickly absorbed by the carbon nanotube casing, preventing most cases of overheating and allowing for faster shots than its ballistic counterpart.

The medigun fires a stream of nano particles at the target which heals damaged tissue and ligaments. This device by CryoTech Industries is revolutionary in being lightweight and compact enough to be fit in your pocket. It is not intended to heal serious wounds and you should seek further medical help from a registered medic terminal.
Created using a reverse temperature polarization technique, this energy rifle fires at a faster rate and deals stamina damage.
Capable of mining the highest class rocks available, this precision instrument mines the resources necessary for the most advanced production techniques.
Designed by Dominion engineers, this weapon was intended for the population control of the rapidly reproducing xenomorph species.
Created by American Enterprises, this amazing piece of technology is capable of killing Xenomorphs and humans alike, without requiring the same effort and ability as other weapons.

Utilizing a special type of 9mm round, this illegal modification of the Zanathid 5 Inflex is capable of piercing any time of armor on the market. Meant as a weapon able to be used against those with significant armor, it certainly packs a punch.
A reward for backing our Kickstarter campaign, this rifle will make your dedication to the game clear.
Utilizing advanced energy weaponry, this deployable object allows you to build stationary defense positions, attacking targets based on circumstances that you define in the confugration.
As standard a handgun as will be found in The Dominion, the Inflex can take standard 9mm ammo. Originally produced by Isotech, it is now widely constructed (often illegally) due to its wide design.
Remaining virtually unchanged for 300 years, 9mm rounds have long since proven their durability in comparison to more high tech variants.
Energy cells consist of plasma which is - in compressed form - able to destabilize the target upon impact. They are slowly but surely replacing traditional projectiles as the ammunition of choice.
Standard issue 7.62mm rounds used in all major rifles.
Energy cells consist of plasma which is - in compressed form - able to destabilize the target upon impact. They are slowly but surely replacing traditional projectiles as the ammunition of choice.
Energy cells consist of plasma which is - in compressed form - able to destabilize the target upon impact. They are slowly but surely replacing traditional projectiles as the ammunition of choice.
Standard 5.54mm rounds used in a variety of small arms.
7.62mm rounds reinforced with special steel to provide extra penetrating power.
7.62mm rounds with small electromagnets inside that activate upon impact, creating small pulses which damage machines.
A relatively new innovation, biocells are a disposable energy supply which can interface directly with your body's neural system, and recharge the energy supply used to power augmentations.
A small, disposable treatment kit. Healing times are long, but the production is cheap.
An average sized treatment kit. Provides standard healing times with good item production costs.
A large treatment kit, containing sufficient materials to stabilize and maintain a patient's health quickly and efficiently. Healing is fast, but production is not cheap.
A fully stocked treatment kit, including surgical implements and a range of experimental medicines. This kit provides the best healing times, but is expensive in production.

A portable means of providing an intramuscular infusion of restorative nanomachines, utilizing freon gas compressed to 1500 atmospheres. Requires care to ensure nanomachines are infused into areas that have a high concentration of blood capillaries to ensure maximum dispersal rates.

An advanced version of a means of providing an intramuscular infusion of restorative nanomachines, utilizing freon gas compressed to 1500 atmospheres. Due to improvements in the nanomachines utilized, the autoinjector can be administered to any part of the body with no decrease in efficacy, as well as have a higher rate of healing overall. As this is still a prototype, it has not been made available to the general public for use and production.

Containing a single dose of adrenaline, this item was originally designed for the military for use in combat to give soldiers the strength to endure strenuous physical activity for a period longer than they would normally be able to. The adrenaline is injected intramuscularly by a disposable canister of compressed freon.

Containing electrolytes saturated with organic energy particles, this item was originally designed for the military for use in combat to give soldiers a near immediate infusion of bioenergy. Due to the relatively small amount of bioenergy it replenishes, it was prescribed to be used only in emergencies The electrolytes are injected intramuscularly by a disposable canister of compressed freon.
Feeding off the body's bio-electrical energy supply, this gadget will illuminate dark areas.
Interfacing directly with the human respiratory system, the stamina amplification channels into the bio-electrical energy supply also, thus giving the user far greater endurance.
A simple directional lamp which mounts on the shoulder for low tech illumination. Runs off the body's bio-electrical supply.
This augmentation uses a scarcely understood procedure of transforming bio-electrical charges in the body into fresh tissue, thus performing a rapid, albeit inefficient, healing process.

An experimental device, the shield device projects a protective bubble around the user, which offers armor, shielding attributes or both. The amount of armor vs. shielding can be adjusted via a slider. You can either have full armor, full shielding or a value inbetween. Feeds off the body's bio-electrical supply.

Through careful manipulation of the Vortex Network, this special augmentation will allow the user access to locked apartments. During apartment entrance, this augmentation will be capable of scanning the Vortex Aura, recording the targeting information to a ticket in the user's inventory. Accessing a special menu while at an Apartment Complex will allow the user to hack into the apartment and steal goods from inside.

This latest product to be invented by the engineers in Vortex Incorporated, informally dubbed the 'vortex-on-the-go'. It requires a full biocell upon activation and consumes a large amount of bioenergy during the countdown in order to power a compact, high-powered emitter which envelops the user with a considerable amount of vortex particles, and create a strong enough link to the vortex network.
Using advanced geological surveying techniques, this augmentation will allow you to locate specific mineral deposits and mine them.

Utilizing the fallen government's Universal Positioning System, this augmentation will allow you to locate specific individuals, regardless of where they are in the galaxy. The precision of the scan depends on how long they remain in the same area. Through special modifications made to the technology, this augmentation can also view the history of any apartment safe.
The Advanced Civilian armor was designed for deep planetary mining operations. Although designed for civilian use, this heavy armor has seen many military campaigns as well.
The MT-27 Ballistics armor was originally designed for use in militias. This mass-produced armor offers more than adequate protection for reasonable prices.

The Tactical Systems armor is the basis for the most advanced armor available today. Its unique blend of lightweight compounds and an easy to repair design has inspired many to further develop the system.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Defense armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Ethereal armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Patrol armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Pressured armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

The favorite of vehicle crewmen, scouts and certain special forces, Special Operations Armor is a hardy Dominion standard that has seen relatively little innovation since the days before handheld energy weapons.

Used widely by Dominion troops since the first Necar’s Field Conflict, some veterans swear by the fit and feel of this classic armor. Interlocking tensile and ceramic plates designed to make enemy ballistics nonfatal still provide mild protection against heat.

The Pythica S1 armors have been engineered to be lighter than the Pythica Battle armor series, allowing for slightly better endurance. Based on the crystal lattice technology used in many heavier armors, this armor uses less material for a lighter wear.

The Pythica Sustained Battle series of armor is the revolutionized self of its earlier Ceremonial versions. It provides unrivalled protection, with even higher density made possible by further research into crystal lattice technology.

Originally designed by CryoTech Industries for use in front-line triages, automated injectors throughout the inner suit of this armor provide spot-treatment for wounds. This armor became combat-capable with the addition of an ablative layer above the suit.

Developed by CryoTech Industries to give front-line patrols a boost of endurance for long or exhausting deployments, this suit has found niche uses among those who prefer sprightliness over protective capacity.

CryoTech Industries created this automated suit to address growing concerns among enlisted FDC that mission-critical bio-augmentations were failing in the middle of operations. It replaces positively charged ions with negatives in the blood via nanite injectors.

With the inevitable risk of injury during deep space mining, CryoTech Industries engineered this armor to help regain consciousness in the event of a disaster. Redeveloped with lighter wear for use in combat, this armor can help the user better keep their mind intact during a battle.

The favorite of assassins, the light Hypobaric Armor strategically releases mildly toxic muscle relaxants to steady aim and focus its wearer. This slows the user’s metabolism, reducing bioelectric output.
This armor, based on CryoTech Vitality Suits, foregoes strictly legal serums for added regenerative capability, though one’s immune system rebels against these stronger synthetic drugs over time.

Venom armor uses strong amphetamine injections to accelerate one’s metabolism, producing extra bioelectric energy, but prolonged over-oxygenation can lead to lightheadedness and ultimately panic or catatonia in its user.

Designed by enterprising Brotherhood engineers sympathetic to the plight of their front-line kin, this armor includes automated systems that suppress silly, overambitious immune responses, purging one’s resistance to combat stimulants.

Devised using the same technology that powers augmentations, practical powered armor harmlessly extracts human bio-energy to power systems that enhance combat capability, without the need for a heavy battery.

Devised using the same technology that powers augmentations, practical powered armor harmlessly extracts human bio-energy to power systems that enhance combat capability, without the need for a heavy battery.

Devised using the same technology that powers augmentations, practical powered armor harmlessly extracts human bio-energy to power systems that enhance combat capability, without the need for a heavy battery.

Devised using the same technology that powers augmentations, practical powered armor harmlessly extracts human bio-energy to power systems that enhance combat capability, without the need for a heavy battery.

The need to stay in a healthy mental state during combat has caused PreMet Buffer armor to become a popular choice against the striking blows caused by rubber bullet and high pain weaponry. The user will find themselves much tougher to break in terms of mental stability.

The need to stay in a healthy mental state during combat has caused PreMet Contact armor to become a popular choice against the striking blows caused by rubber bullet and high pain weaponry. The user will find themselves much tougher to break in terms of mental stability.

The need to stay in a healthy mental state during combat has caused PreMet Collision armor to become a popular choice against the striking blows caused by rubber bullet and high pain weaponry. The user will find themselves much tougher to break in terms of mental stability.

The need to stay in a healthy mental state during combat has caused PreMet Impact armor to become a popular choice against the striking blows caused by rubber bullet and high pain weaponry. The user will find themselves much tougher to break in terms of mental stability.

Incorporating a layer of non-newtonian fluid, Dilatant armor has a “bend or break” counteractive effect on incoming projectiles. This system is very light compared to the ablative plating of most armors.

Aramid fiber has revolutionized armor to become durable versus high speed projectiles and heated beams. Utilizing a layer of high strength polymer blends, this armor is able to absorb the lion’s share of most impacts against it.

Infensus Minimalist Armor was released after many complained that the Essentials line was still impractically heavy for cramped or arduous conditions. Minimalist Armor retains only the reflective shell of its heavier cousins.

It’s no surprise that Infensus Battle Armor is so burdensome, given its origin design, the space suit. Sharing a need to regulate, reduce and shed heat rapidly, IBA has since undergone dozens of redesigns for use in combat against new-age energy weapons.

Modern threats require modern solutions, and this cutting-edge energy dispersal armor is that solution. Marketed to corporate commandos going up against their technophilic competitors, it has a glossy, futuristic aesthetic.

Upon the discovery of the xenomorph colony on Necars Field, and the subsequent discovery of the incredible resilience of the alien carapace, research began immediately to study potential military applications of the procured xenomorph components. The result is this unique set of armor, whose organic appearance reflects the origin of its component parts.

Part of the set of prototype armor stolen from the Galactic Intelligence Service by the organization colloquially known as the Men in Black, and subsequently released for purchase in limited quantities in order to sustain the MIB's continued rebellion.
To top off your Halloween costume, this helmet will truly make you look as threatening as a Black Shuck.
To top off your Halloween costume, this helmet will truly make you look as threatening as an Echion.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Stabilized armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

The Pythica Durable Battle series of armor is the revolutionized self of its earlier Ceremonial versions. It provides unrivalled protection, with even higher density made possible by further research into crystal lattice technology.
A blend of CryoTech Industries’ four main lines of combat armor, this armor employs miniature nano-injectors of all varieties to treat physical fatigue in each of its forms.
This sleek pair of acetate frames are both light-weight and comfortable.
The classic design of these glasses is still a hit in the modern Dominion, and gives an elegant look of sophistication
A little bit retro, a little bit contemporary, they work for pretty much everyone.
The modern rectangle-shaped glasses from ALM designs are known throughout the Global Dominion.
A new era brings new designs. These are ultra modern and ultra light optical protectors.
A classic pair of unisex semi-rimless glasses with a stylish monel metal finish.
Made for all outdoor activities or just looking good sipping a latte at Moes bar.

The sunglasses made popular by the agents of the Galactic Intelligence Service. Despite being purpose-made for the GIS, it has been released for purchase by the average citizen in limited supply in order due to popular demand.

Because bears are too hard to train, this extra-heavy armor requires powered servos as well as the strength of its user to function. Locking, white-hot machinery and anabolic injections make Leech Armor usable, as long as bodily harm is no object.

Created from a variation of the Exile armor, this resilient orange armor reminds one of the Halloween season, hence it's name.

The result is this unique set of armor, whose organic appearance reflects the origin of its component parts.

Part of the set of prototype armor stolen from the Galactic Intelligence Service by the organization colloquially known as the Men in Black, and subsequently released for purchase in limited quantities in order to sustain the MIB's continued rebellion.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Stabilized armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

The Pythica Durable Battle series of armor is the revolutionized self of its earlier Ceremonial versions. It provides unrivalled protection, with even higher density made possible by further research into crystal lattice technology.
A blend of CryoTech Industries’ four main lines of combat armor, this armor employs miniature nano-injectors of all varieties to treat physical fatigue in each of its forms.

Because bears are too hard to train, this extra-heavy armor requires powered servos as well as the strength of its user to function. Locking, white-hot machinery and anabolic injections make Leech Armor usable, as long as bodily harm is no object.

Devised using the same technology that powers augmentations, practical powered armor harmlessly extracts human bio-energy to power systems that enhance combat capability, without the need for a heavy battery.

The need to stay in a healthy mental state during combat has caused PreMet Tremor armor to become a popular choice against the striking blows caused by rubber bullet and high pain weaponry. The user will find themselves much tougher to break in terms of mental stability.

Aramid fiber has revolutionized armor to become durable versus high speed projectiles and heated beams. Utilizing a layer of high strength polymer blends, this armor is able to absorb the lion’s share of most impacts against it.

A stripped-down version of the Heavy Infensus Battle armor, the “Essentials” line foregoes a flush coolant system for greater speed and maneuverability, though it retains the armor’s heavy plating designed to turn, disperse and shed heat.
Created from a variation of the Exile armor, this resilient orange armor reminds one of the Halloween season, hence it's name.
Created from a variation of the Exile armor, this resilient skeleton armor reminds one of the Halloween season, hence it's name
A reward for backing our Kickstarter campaign, these shoulder pads will make your dedication to the game clear.
The Advanced Civilian armor was designed for deep planetary mining operations. Although designed for civilian use, this heavy armor has seen many military campaigns as well.
The MT-27 Ballistics armor was originally designed for use in militias. This mass-produced armour offers more than adequate protection for reasonable prices.

The Tactical Systems armor is the basis for the most advanced armor available today. Its unique blend of lightweight compounds and an easy to repair design has inspired many to further develop the system.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Defense armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

After Locans Systems was edged out of the armor market, larger corporations took over their designs. The remade Locans Pressured armors retain their resistance against higher mass ballistics, while using materials that allow them to be viable in regular combat.

The favorite of vehicle crewmen, scouts and certain special forces, Special Operations Armor is a hardy Dominion standard that has seen relatively little innovation since the days before handheld energy weapons.

Used widely by Dominion troops since the first Necar’s Field Conflict, some veterans swear by the fit and feel of this classic armor. Interlocking tensile and ceramic plates designed to make enemy ballistics nonfatal still provide mild protection against heat.

The Pythica S1 armors have been engineered to be lighter than the Pythica Battle armor series, allowing for slightly better endurance. Based on the crystal lattice technology used in many heavier armors, this armor uses less material for a lighter wear.

The Pythica Sustained Battle series of armor is the revolutionized self of its earlier Ceremonial versions. It provides unrivalled protection, with even higher density made possible by further research into crystal lattice technology.

Originally designed by CryoTech Industries for use in front-line triages, automated injectors throughout the inner suit of this armor provide spot-treatment for wounds. This armor became combat-capable with the addition of an ablative layer above the suit.

Developed by CryoTech Industries to give front-line patrols a boost of endurance for long or exhausting deployments, this suit has found niche uses among those who prefer sprightliness over protective capacity.

CryoTech Industries created this automated suit to address growing concerns among enlisted FDC that mission-critical bio-augmentations were failing in the middle of operations. It replaces positively charged ions with negatives in the blood via nanite injectors.

With the inevitable risk of injury during deep space mining, CryoTech Industries engineered this armor to help regain consciousness in the event of a disaster. Redeveloped with lighter wear for use in combat, this armor can help the user better keep their mind intact during a battle.

The favorite of assassins, the light Hypobaric Armor strategically releases mildly toxic muscle relaxants to steady aim and focus its wearer. This slows the user’s metabolism, reducing bioelectric output.
This armor, based on CryoTech Vitality Suits, foregoes strictly legal serums for added regenerative capability, though one’s immune system rebels against these stronger synthetic drugs over time.

Venom armor uses strong amphetamine injections to accelerate one’s metabolism, producing extra bioelectric energy, but prolonged over-oxygenation can lead to lightheadedness and ultimately panic or catatonia in its user.

Designed by enterprising Brotherhood engineers sympathetic to the plight of their front-line kin, this armor includes automated systems that suppress silly, overambitious immune responses, purging one’s resistance to combat stimulants.

The heavily carapaced forelimb of the Carcinus genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. The claws on its forelimbs consist of a large amount of organic minerals which serve to maintain its impeccable sharpness.
The heavyset head of the Carcinus genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. The carbonite reinforced cranium of the Carcinus provides ample protection to its cerebral matter.

The section of extremely thick chitinous carapace from the dorsal regions of the Carcinus genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. This is where the carapace is the thickest for the Carcinus's body, as it is meant to protect the central nervous system located just beneath.

The muscular forelimb of the Behemoth genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. Although the carapace encasing the muscle within is not particularly thick, the molecular structure of the minerals in the claws gives a strength that rivals that of diamonds.

The immense head of the Behemoth genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. The size and shape of the cranial regions of the Behemoth's skull reflects the tremendous amount of brain matter enshrouded within.

The severed tail of a member of the Behemoth genus of xenomorphs from Necars Field. The tail contains significant muscle mass as it is used by the Behemoth to steady and balance itself whenever it walks.
The forcefully removed carapace of a xenomorph. Still has some sinewy muscle fibre and fluid-secreting glands attached.
The eyes of a xenomorph. Their biological structure allow these xenomorphs to see just as well in complete darkness as in the day.
Carefully extracted from the skull of a xenomorph. The brains of these creatures are much sought-after by scientists for studies into xenomorph intelligence.
The claw of a xenomorph. It is always carefully removed from the xenomorph carcass to prevent damage to the carapace, which is popular for refinement and production of local souvenirs.

Severed head of the Mantis genus of xenomorphs. Although not particularly large to allow this xenomorph to be effectively flight-capable, it is a rich source of xenomorphic fluids as all of its endocrine glands are located here.
The middle portion of the thoracic region of the Mantis genus of xenomorphs. This part of the xenomorph is extremely muscular, allowing the mantis to thrust its caudal sting with devastating force.

The rear-most portion of the thoracic region of the Mantis genus of xenomorphs. This part of the xenomorph has the caudal sting attached to it. Although it does not contain any venom, the sting is reinforced with enough precious minerals to allow it to resist damage.
The fluid extracted from various xenomorph parts, particularly those that contain fluid-producing glands.
Extracted from the outermost layer of a xenomorph's carapace, which is primarily made of carbonite which has proven to be very effective as a reinforcing agent.
Proteins extracted from the muscle tissues of xenomorphs.
Extracted from the claws, spikes, and stings of the various xenomorphs, which are naturally coated with a thin layer of this mineral which gives it its incredible resilience and robustness.
The natural respiratory process of xenomorphs produces heavy water (water with deuterium in place of normal hydrogen molecules), which is then excreted through the intestinal tract.
Hemolymph fills the internal cavities of the xenomorphs, acting as both blood and interstitial fluid. The hemolymph is pumped around the body both by the heart and the xenomorph's muscular movements.
As the mantis has a dual circulatory system that utilizes both hemolymph and blood, the two fluids often mix into a bloody mix of what appears to be slime mixed with significant traces of blood.
The glands of xenomorphs are much sought after for the rare secretions produced that appear to have strong medicinal properties, according to preliminary studies made by biologists on Necars Field.
